Program: Discovery
Title: Hope for an HIV vaccine
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwl6
Last Broadcast Date: 13 January 1996
Why a live virus is probably our best hope for a vaccine against AIDS. American researchers believe they might have developed a safe live version of the virus. Also in the programme how astronomers are drawing a new map of the universe which shows that there is order in nature.